    {
      "_id": "crXV18abZr2DcEh8",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
      "name": "Regurgitate",
      "sort": 1100000,
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>The tarnworm can violently regurgitate a creature or boulder it has swallowed to make a ranged Strike. The Strike deals bludgeoning damage depending on the size of the projectile: Tiny deals [[/r {2d6+13}[bludgeoning]]]{2d6+13}, Small [[/r {3d6+13}[bludgeoning]]]{3d6+13}, Medium [[/r {4d6+13}[bludgeoning]]]{4d6+13}, Large [[/r {5d6+13}[bludgeoning]]]{5d6+13}, and Huge [[/r {6d6+13}[bludgeoning]]]{6d6+13}. A regurgitated creature takes falling damage from the height of the target or from 20 feet, whichever is greater.</p>\n<p>Boulders occupy space in the worm's stomach as a creature of equivalent size, and tarnworm often have several boulders swallowed. A tarnworm can use a single action to swallow a new boulder.</p>"
        },
